      <div class="msgContentFrame">Playing this game is an interesting experience. From a developmental standpoint there are some aspects that were hastily slapped together at the last minute (and I'm not bothered by them, they will be fixed). Then there are other aspects where there's an attention to detail rarely or never seen in other games. I really appreciate the work SE put into the characters, their clothing and their facial expressions. Last night I was in an exp party in the TamTara Deepcroft. The Black Efts there do an AoE bind move and I took notice of the facial expressions and posture the characters have with this status. I thought it was so cool, check out this screenshot: <br /> <br /><a href="http://img219.imageshack.us/img219/1775/boundpng.png" title="http://img219.imageshack.us/img219/1775/boundpng.png" rel="external nofollow">http://img219.imageshack.us/img219/1775/boundpng.png</a> <br /> <br />It looks like a cut scene doesn't it? I find it impressive that the game produces images like this in real time in ordinary situations. SE's devs deserve credit for a job well done with the character models. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 21st 2010  3:54pm by TauuOfSiren </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXIV Lalafell PHY36: WVR26, CON25, TAN20, BTN15 <br />FFXI Tarutaru: WHM75, PLD75, BST75, SMN37, SCH37, WAR37, NIN37 (retired)</div></div>
