      <div class="msgContentFrame">Agreed... but I still want my purple hair! <br /> <br />Seriously though, yeah, there are so many little details that you notice when you look (or that occasionly jump out at you... and eat you) that it makes me glad I'm taking the time to do everything at the pace I am. <br />Especially Botany... and I NEVER would have guessed coming in how much I would enjoy that, but going around and searching the world for logging and harvest points exposed me to some places and things that I'm really looking forward to seeing with my combat class... and killing.  :P <br /> <br />If you get a chance, at night near Camp Bloodshore, head out to the cliffs and stand on the edge (maybe get some fishing in)... watch the reflection of the moon on the water.  What I noticed about it just floored me, as I sat there fishing throughout the night... that ripply reflection MOVES over the course of the night, tracking with the moon.  It just looked so natural, I didn't even realize it until half the night was over and I was like, &quot;Hey, wasn't I casting INTO the reflection a while back... now it's over... IT MOVED!&quot; <br /> <br />The other stuff will be fixed over time, I'm not stressing it either OP.  Something tells me that the people who made that reflection, and put the expressions on those Lala faces, and made pretty much anything with eyes blink, genuinely care enough about the game that they'll get it together. <br /> <br />Keep having fun and being pleasantly surprised! <br /> <br />Sincerly <br />Ailys Foxglove <br />-Kashuan</div>
